x4freetext: Cross sections and angular distributions of fragments
in the fission of Pu-238,Pu-242 and Am-241 by neutrons
of energies from 0.45 up to 3.6 MeV
Tritium target on zirconium backing with
Proton energy from 1.4 up to 4.8 MeV.
Angular uncertainty of neutron beam was +-3.5 degrees
Registration efficiency was checked by measurement of
calibrated Cm-244 layer spontaneous fission fragments.
Expansion on Legendre polynomials of even power
Corrected for background and admixtures of other
Distance between neutron source and sample was
equal to 50 mm, distance between sample and detector
Fission fragments were detected at angles 0, 22.5,
Angular uncertainty of fission fragments registration
Max. error due to non-homogeneity and
Correction in REACTION coding in SAN 008,
Upper -> lower case. BIB information was added.
